quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,58,"So he broke them into pieces, except the biggest of them, so that they might come back to it.",""
  21,59,"They said, “Who has done this to our gods? He is indeed one of the wrongdoers.”",""
  21,60,"They said, “We heard a young man, speaking ill of them, who is called Abraham.”",""
  21,61,"They said, “Bring him then before the eyes of the people, so that they may witness [his trial]<sup>23</sup>.”","[23] Or his confession about what he did."
  21,62,"They said, “Are you the one who did this to our gods, O Abraham?”",""
  21,63,"He said, “Rather, it was this biggest one who did it. So ask them, if they can speak!”",""
  21,64,"So they turned back to one another, and said, “Indeed, it is you who are the wrongdoers.”",""
  21,65,"Then they turned to their obstinacy<sup>24</sup>, [saying], “You already know that they cannot speak.”","[24] After first admitting their error."
  21,66,"Abraham said, “Do you then worship besides Allah that which can neither benefit nor harm you in the least?",""
  21,67,"Fie upon you<sup>25</sup> and upon all that you worship besides Allah! Do you not have any sense?”","[25] An expression of anger and displeasure."
  21,68,"They said, “Burn him and avenge your gods if you must do something.”",""
  21,69,"We said, “O fire, be cool and safe for Abraham.”<sup>26</sup>","[26] It is reported in an authentic Hadīth that Abraham said, while being thrown into the fire, “Allah is sufficient for us and He is the best Protector.”"
  21,70,"They plotted to harm him, but We made them the worst losers.",""
  21,71,"And We saved him and Lot [and brought him] to the land<sup>27</sup> that we have blessed for all people.","[27] i.e., the Levant. Abraham and his nephew, Lot, were saved from their enemy Nimrod and his people, as they migrated from the land of Babel, Iraq to Jerusalem."
  21,72,"And We gave him Isaac, and then Jacob, a grandson, and We made all of them righteous.",""
